Viwandani MCA Samwel Nyang'wara, who tabled the motion for the Nairobi Governor's impeachment, has been discharged from three assembly committees.Nyang'wara has been discharged from the Business, Health Services and Trade, Tourism and Cooperatives committees.Majority leader Elias Otieno, who is Kileleshwa MCA, informed Speaker Alex Magelo of the developments in a letter on Wednesday.Nyang'wara tabled is motion at the assembly on Tuesday as his first attempt on September 29 turned chaotic.But ward representatives still caused drama despite a warning by Magelo, who said those responsible for the first incident would be punished.[VIDEO] Nairobi MCAs throw punches as Kidero impeachment motion tabledRead: Kidero impeachment motion tabled despite fracas at Nairobi assemblyThe motion, that arose from claims Kidero has violated the constitution and misappropriated funds, was approved last Thursday.The Speaker committed it to the House Business Committee that will allocate it time for debate.The motion requires the support of a third of all members to be tabled. Nairobi has 127 MCAs so it would take 87 MCAs to impeach Kidero. At least 56 Cord and Jubilee MCAs signed the petition.